stimulus: Welcome to the experiment. Press any key to begin and to advance the instructions.

Welcome! Today you are going to play 6 different rounds of a decision-making game.

Use the mouse to click next to continue.
You will start with a practice round to learn the rules.
Your goal in this round is to give out sports equipment to kids.

The kids only like some of the equipment.

On each turn, you will see a piece of sports equipment.

You need to decide whether to give it to the kids or not.

You can give them the equipment by pressing 1 and choose not to give it to them by pressing 0.


Press "1."
Press "0."

If you give them a piece of equipment they like, they will be happy!

But if you give them a piece of equipment they do not like, they will be sad.

You will earn points based on how you make kids feel.

If you make them happy, you will WIN anywhere from 1 - 9 points,

but if you make them sad, you will LOSE anywhere from 1 - 9 points.

You will see how many points you won or lost in the center of the screen.

Here is what you would see if you won 6 points:

6

The text is GREEN because you WON points.

And here is what you would see if you lost 4 points:

-4

The text is RED because you LOST points.

Some of the equipment will make the kids VERY happy or sad.

These pieces of equipment will make you win or lose LOTS of points.

Other pieces of equipment will only make the kids a little happy or sad.

These pieces of equipment will make you win or lose small amounts of points.

If you choose not to give them the equipment, you will not win or lose any points.

However, in the center of the screen, you will see the number of points you WOULD HAVE won or lost if you had given them the equipment.

Here is what you might see if you did not give the equipment to the kids but it would have made them happy:

  7  

Remember, in this case, you would not win or lose ANY points because you did not give them the equipment.

The text is GREY because you earned ZERO points.

However, choosing to give the kids the equipment would have made you win points. The box around the text is RED because you chose the worse option.

Here is what you might see if you did not give the equipment to the kids but it would have made them sad:

  -8  

Remember, in this case, you would not win or lose ANY points because you did not give them the equipment.

The text is GREY because you earned ZERO points.

Choosing to give the kids the equipment would have made you lose points. The box around the text is GREEN because you chose the better option.

You will have 3 seconds to make each choice. Try to respond before time runs out!

You will lose 5 points each time you do not make a response.
This is just a practice round, but in the real game, your bonus payment will depend on your total number of points.

Remember, you can give them the equipment by pressing 1 and choose not to give it to them by pressing 0.


Press "1."
Press "0."
You earned -8 points in the practice round!

It's almost time to start the real game.

Before you start, we're going to ask you a few questions about how the game works.

True or False?

If you see a number in GREY, that means you earned that many points.

That's right! If you see a grey number, it means you earned ZERO points.
The grey numbers show the points you WOULD HAVE earned if you had made the other choice.

True or False?

You will have as much time as you want to make each choice.
That's right! You will only have 3 seconds to make each choice.

True or False?

You should use the '1' and '0' keys to make your choices.
That's right! You should use the '1' and '0' keys to make each choice.

It's now time to start the real game.

Do your best, because the points you earn in the next rounds will influence your bonus payment.
Your goal in this round is to take care of lots of animals.

Some animals want to be pet, while other animals want to be left alone.

On each turn, you will see an animal.

You need to decide whether to pet it or not.

You can pet the animal by pressing 1 and leave the animal alone by pressing 0.


Press "1."
Press "0."

If you pet an animal that wants to be pet, you will make it feel happy!

But if you pet an animal that wants to be left alone, you will make it feel angry.

You will earn points based on how you made the animal feel.

If you made it feel happy, you will WIN anywhere from 1 - 9 points,

but if you made it feel angry, you will LOSE anywhere from 1 - 9 points.

You will see how many points you won or lost in the center of the screen.

Here is what you would see if you won 5 points:

5

And here is what you would see if you lost 3 points:

-3

Some animals will become very happy or very angry.

These animals will make you win or lose LOTS of points.

Other animals have less strong feelings.

These animals will make you win or lose small amounts of points.

If you choose to leave the animal alone, you will not win or lose any points.

However, in the center of the screen, you will see the number of points you WOULD HAVE won or lost if you had pet the animal.

Here is what you might see if you did not pet the animal but the animal wanted to be pet:

  6  

Remember, in this case, you would not win or lose ANY points because you did not pet the animal.

Try to make the best choice for each animal because

at the end of the game, you will earn bonus money based on how many points you earned.

You will have 3 seconds to make each choice. Try to respond before time runs out!

You will lose 5 points each time you do not make a response.

You have completed the round!

In this round, you earned 82 points!
Now it's time to play another round.

On each turn, you will see a vehicle.

You need to decide whether to take your friend for a ride or not.

You can take your friend for a ride in the vehicle by pressing 1 and skip the ride by pressing 0.


Press "1."
Press "0."

If you take them for a ride in a vehicle they like, they will be thrilled!

But if you take them for a ride in a vehicle they do not like, they will be upset.

You will earn points based on how you made your friend feel.

If you made him thrilled, you will WIN anywhere from 1 - 9 points,

but if you made him upset, you will LOSE anywhere from 1 - 9 points.

You will see how many points you won or lost in the center of the screen.

Here is what you would see if you won 5 points:

5

And here is what you would see if you lost 3 points:

-3

Some vehicles will make your friend REALLY thrilled or upset.

These vehicles will make you win or lose LOTS of points.

Other vehicles will only make him feel a little thrilled or upset.

These vehicles will make you win or lose small amounts of points.

If you choose to skip the ride, you will not win or lose any points.

However, in the center of the screen, you will see the number of points you WOULD HAVE won or lost if you had taken your friend for a ride.

Here is what you might see if you did not take your friend for a ride but he would have enjoyed it:

  6  

Remember, in this case, you would not win or lose ANY points because you skipped the ride.

Try to make the best choice for each vehicle because

at the end of the game, you will earn bonus money based on how many points you earned.

You will have 3 seconds to make each choice. Try to respond before time runs out!

You will lose 5 points each time you do not make a response.

You have completed the round!

In this round, you earned 104 points!
